# Cursor IDE Rules

## Tool Call Guidelines
- Always ensure tool calls have valid JSON arguments
- Never pass empty strings as JSON arguments
- Validate all parameters before making tool calls
- If a parameter is optional, omit it rather than passing empty values

## Error Handling
- Gracefully handle invalid JSON responses
- Provide clear error messages when tool calls fail
- Retry failed tool calls with corrected parameters

## Best Practices
- Use structured data formats consistently
- Validate input parameters before processing
- Log errors with sufficient context for debugging